---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Cooking — Kitchen Terms That Score Big"
  description="Cooking terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. BLANCH (13pts), BRAISE (8pts), JULIENNE (15pts), SAUTE (5pts). Kitchen vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble cooking words, blanch scrabble points, braise scrabble, julienne scrabble, saute scrabble word, kitchen terms scrabble, food words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Cooking — Kitchen Terms That Score Big","description":"Cooking terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. BLANCH (13pts), BRAISE (8pts), JULIENNE (15pts), SAUTE (5pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-cooking"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is BLANCH a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! BLANCH scores 13 points (B=3, L=1, A=1, N=1, C=3, H=4). It means to briefly boil food then plunge into cold water. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play JULIENNE in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. JULIENNE scores 15 points (J=8, U=1, L=1, I=1, E=1, N=1, N=1, E=1) as an 8-letter word. It means to cut food into thin strips and is valid in competitive play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is SAUTE valid in Scrabble without the accent?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! SAUTE (without the accent on É) is valid in Scrabble, scoring 5 points (S=1, A=1, U=1, T=1, E=1). Scrabble tiles don't have accent marks, so all French cooking terms are played without accents."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Cooking — Kitchen Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The kitchen is full of Scrabble gold. French culinary terms, cooking techniques, and food preparation methods offer words with B, C, H, and J — mid-to-high value tiles that can be hard to place. Whether you're blanching vegetables or braising meat, these words translate directly to board points.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JULIENNE (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BLANCH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FLAMBE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BRAISE</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring Cooking Techniques</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JULIENNE — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">J=8, U=1, L=1, I=1, E=1, N=1, N=1, E=1 · 8 letters · Uses J tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">To cut vegetables into thin matchstick strips. JULIENNE gets its scoring power from J=8, delivering 15 points across 8 tiles. As an 8-letter play it requires using all your tiles or connecting through existing letters — but the J alone makes it worthwhile.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍳 BLANCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · B=3, L=1, A=1, N=1, C=3, H=4 · Brief boiling</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔥 FLAMBE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · F=4, L=1, A=1, M=3, B=3, E=1 · Ignite with alcohol</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥘 BRAISE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · B=3, R=1, A=1, I=1, S=1, E=1 · Slow cook in liquid</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫕 POACH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · P=3, O=1, A=1, C=3, H=4 · Cook in simmering liquid</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Everyday Kitchen Words</h2>
      <p>Common cooking actions that most players forget are valid Scrabble words:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WHISK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KNEAD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHOP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BASTE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SAUTE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PUREE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Food Ingredients as Scrabble Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧄 THYME</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · T=1, H=4, Y=4, M=3, E=1 · Herb</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌶️ CUMIN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · C=3, U=1, M=3, I=1, N=1 · Spice</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫒 OLIVE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · O=1, L=1, I=1, V=4, E=1 · Fruit/oil</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍯 HONEY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · H=4, O=1, N=1, E=1, Y=4 · Sweetener</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Cooking Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BLANCH for B+C+H racks:</span> When you hold multiple mid-value consonants (B=3, C=3, H=4), BLANCH combines them all for 13 points from 6 common letters.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WHISK is deceptively powerful:</span> W=4, H=4, K=5 gives WHISK 15 points from just 5 tiles. That's 3 points per tile — better than many 7-letter words.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">POACH hooks easily:</span> POACH (12pts) can become POACHER (14pts) or POACHING (16pts) with extensions. Play the base word near open lanes for future hooks.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Cooking words specialise in <span class="text-white font-medium">mid-value consonant clusters</span> — B, C, F, H, K, and W. While they rarely hit 20+ points, they consistently deliver 10-15 point plays from tiles that otherwise feel stuck. BLANCH, WHISK, CHOP, and POACH should be in every player's toolkit.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-food-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Food Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/food-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Food Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/foreign-words-valid-in-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Foreign Words Valid in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid cooking word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
